{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Search the web for recent papers and techniques on LLM inference latency prediction and simulator calibration. I need information on:\n\n1. **Vidur simulator** (Microsoft) - how it models step times, any calibration techniques\n2. **MIST** - LLM inference serving trace analysis\n3. **Splitwise / DistServe** - how they model inference latency\n4. **vLLM performance modeling** - any papers on predicting vLLM step times\n5. **Trace-driven simulation calibration** - techniques for calibrating DES simulators against real traces\n6. **TTFT prediction in LLM serving** - how systems predict time-to-first-token\n7. **Queueing theory for LLM inference** - M/G/1-PS models or similar for batch inference\n8. **Online calibration / Bayesian optimization for simulator tuning**\n9. **Sarathi, Orca** - batch scheduling and how they model iteration time\n10. **Any techniques for handling the gap between per-step prediction accuracy and end-to-end latency accuracy in simulators**\n\nFor each, provide:\n- Key technique/approach\n- How they handle step time prediction\n- How they handle TTFT prediction\n- Any calibration methodology\n- Relevance to our specific problem (31,906% TTFT error, 33.6% ITL error)\n\nSearch broadly and provide actionable insights."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ET3SZbYVS2gFM9krv6mM9v","session_id":"6b183c99-f74b-427d-be1f-597eb641e46a","uuid":"cd820ecb-30bd-483c-ac74-76dac1bf495e"}
