{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SHpaBAhowLmooVi6rkEN2m","type":"tool_result","content":"# Key Techniques for Simulation Model Calibration\n\nBased on the document metadata and structure, this appears to be a research article on simulation model calibration. However, the provided content is primarily PDF structural data rather than readable text content. I can identify from the metadata that the paper addresses:\n\n**Document Focus:**\nThe work titled \"Simulation model calibration with dynamic stratification and adaptive sampling\" by Jain, Shashaani, and Byon (Journal of Simulation, 2024) covers:\n\n**Key Topics Indicated by Keywords:**\n- Data-driven calibration\n- Heteroscedasticity management\n- Post-stratification methods\n- Trust-region optimization\n\n**Observable Structure:**\nThe document contains 23 pages with extensive cross-references and citations (pages 30-32 contain the references section), suggesting comprehensive coverage of calibration methodologies.\n\n**Limitation:**\nThe PDF stream content provided is compressed and encoded, preventing extraction of specific technical details about:\n1. The dynamic stratification approach specifics\n2. Bayesian optimization comparisons\n3. Adaptive sampling implementation details\n4. Gap-handling techniques\n5. Specific objective functions\n6. Parameter sensitivity analysis methods\n\nTo provide detailed technical responses to your seven questions, I would need access to the uncompressed document text rather than the PDF structure data."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ET3SZbYVS2gFM9krv6mM9v","session_id":"6b183c99-f74b-427d-be1f-597eb641e46a","uuid":"11373f43-1bc2-4355-884e-c2449f81d39a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GYurS9QqFC3P1Jm6kPVLQi","type":"tool_result","content":"# FairBatching's TTFT and Iteration Time Modeling\n\n## 1. TTFT vs Throughput Tradeoff Modeling\n\nFairBatching addresses this fundamental tension through an **envelope-based SLO formulation** rather than direct tradeoff modeling. The system defines per-token deadlines as:\n\n> \"token_ddl_{i,j} = arrival_i + ttft_slo + tpot_slo × j\"\n\nThis monotonic deadline structure enables fair resource allocation without the non-monotonic constraints that plague Time-Between-Tokens metrics, allowing prefill and decode tasks to be scheduled more equitably.\n\n## 2. TTFT Prediction Approach\n\nFairBatching does **not directly predict TTFT**. Instead, it tracks whether requests will meet TTFT deadlines by monitoring accumulated slack time. The system calculates remaining time margins relative to deadline envelopes, enabling proactive admission control through the Prefill Admission Budget (PAB) mechanism.\n\n## 3. Batch Formation's Impact on Latency\n\nThe scheduler uses a **three-phase prioritization strategy**:\n- Urgent decode tasks (high SLO risk)\n- Prefill tasks (critical for TTFT)\n- Non-urgent decode tasks (remaining capacity)\n\nThis dynamic composition prevents the decode starvation and prefill queuing that plague rigid decode-prioritizing systems.\n\n## 4. Iteration Time Modeling\n\nFairBatching employs a **linear execution time model**:\n\n> \"batch_time = a + b*total_new_tokens + c*total_context\"\n\nThis captures both FFN computational cost (token-dependent) and attention memory bandwidth (context-dependent), reducing prediction error from ±5.2% to ±1.3%.\n\n## 5. TTFT Prediction Accuracy\n\nThe paper does **not report direct TTFT prediction accuracy metrics**. However, empirical results show the system achieves 2.29× reduction in P99 TTFT tail latency while maintaining TPOT guarantees, demonstrating effective deadline tracking.\n\n## 6. Iteration Time Characterization\n\nExecution time functions as:\n- **Fixed overhead**: parameter *a* per batch\n- **Variable token cost**: coefficient *b* per new token\n- **Context cost**: coefficient *c* per unit of accumulated context length\n\nThis separates compute-intensive (FFN) from memory-bandwidth-bound (attention) components of inference."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ET3SZbYVS2gFM9krv6mM9v","session_id":"6b183c99-f74b-427d-be1f-597eb641e46a","uuid":"d7b4a847-242f-48d3-bb54-3e4e6e559412"}
