{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FRMvmz8dB67zXwjfsVUfmH","type":"tool_result","content":"# TokenSim's Step Time Prediction Approach vs Vidur\n\n## Accuracy Comparison\n\nTokenSim demonstrates superior accuracy to Vidur. For latency predictions across varying request counts (100-500), TokenSim achieved errors of 2.592%-12.593%, compared to Vidur's 2.371%-12.122%. More notably, TokenSim reached geometric mean errors of **0.109% for throughput and 0.6%-0.337% for P50/P99/max latency** when validated against real vLLM results.\n\n## Iteration Time Modeling\n\nRather than using machine learning regression, TokenSim employs **\"a detailed transformer-oriented simulation model\"** to predict computation runtimes. The system connects batch information to external compute simulators like GenZ, which determines iteration duration based on hardware parameters and batch characteristics.\n\n## Profiling Approach\n\nThe paper does not describe TokenSim as profiling-based. Instead, it uses a **modular architecture where batches are sent to compute simulators** that calculate timing, rather than extracting profiles from prior runs.\n\n## TTFT and ITL Prediction\n\nTokenSim predicts these metrics by simulating continuous batching dynamics. It tracks when requests enter the system (TTFT) and monitors token generation intervals throughout decoding (ITL), capturing realistic queue behavior rather than single-request analysis.\n\n## Key Failure Points in Competitors\n\nThe document identifies that **\"existing simulators yield highly inaccurate performance metrics for dynamic LLM workloads due to their lack of batching support.\"** Vidur relies on random forest regression, introducing additional errors, while LLMServingSim suffers from severe performance limitations.\n\n## Error Accumulation\n\nTokenSim maintains sub-1% end-to-end error on real datasets, suggesting **minimal per-step error accumulation** compared to competitors that experience compounding inaccuracies across iterations."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ET3SZbYVS2gFM9krv6mM9v","session_id":"6b183c99-f74b-427d-be1f-597eb641e46a","uuid":"e05934ea-5746-4e44-895a-3fe292239f85"}
