{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HP7ER3HSo8inoHyjDCH3Ls","type":"tool_result","content":"# FairBatching's Linear Execution Time Model\n\n## 1. Core Formula\n\nThe complete model is: **batch_time = a + b×total_new_tokens + c×total_context**\n\nWhere `a` represents fixed per-batch overhead, `b` captures token processing costs, and `c` models KV cache access overhead.\n\n## 2. Calibration Method\n\nParameters are determined offline using historical performance data, then continuously refined during operation. The document states the system uses \"linear regression\" via an \"automated testing framework\" that profiles runtime behavior for each model-GPU combination.\n\n## 3. Accuracy Achievement\n\nThe linear approach reduces prediction error to ±1.3%, compared to ±5.2% from naive token-only budgeting. This improvement stems from accounting for context length, since \"attention operators...involve substantial additional access to the KV cache, a cost proportional to the total context length.\"\n\n## 4. FFN vs. Attention Decomposition\n\nThe model implicitly decomposes through coefficients: the `b` term captures feed-forward network scaling with new tokens, while `c×total_context` represents memory-bandwidth-bound attention operations that scale with cumulative sequence length across all batch requests.\n\n## 5. Prefill Admission Budget (PAB) Connection\n\nPAB calculates how many additional prefill tokens fit within a new request's TTFT deadline by: estimating total batches executable within the window, reserving resources for urgent decode tasks, subtracting existing workload costs, then converting remaining time into token capacity using the `(b+c)` factors.\n\n## 6. Chunked Prefill Impact\n\nChunked prefill inherently fits this model—each chunk's execution time follows the same linear formula, allowing the scheduler to pack smaller prefill segments into remaining batch capacity without reformulating the cost function.\n\n## 7. TTFT Decomposition Insight\n\nThe paper emphasizes that TTFT comprises queuing delay plus prefill execution time, making fairness problematic under decode-prioritizing schedulers that constrain batch capacity uniformly regardless of whether prefill tasks are waiting."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ET3SZbYVS2gFM9krv6mM9v","session_id":"6b183c99-f74b-427d-be1f-597eb641e46a","uuid":"e6873f1b-3120-45dc-9de8-d97edc241f01"}
