{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_017JVYWQ3QWoopwDBcVVJTdv","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01P6Ej2XNqoDsak2YwJq9xnV","name":"WebFetch","input":{"url":"https://dl.acm.org/doi/fullHtml/10.1145/3533271.3561755","prompt":"Extract the key techniques for calibrating multi-agent simulation models using Bayesian optimization. Specifically:\n1. What distance metrics do they use between simulation and real output?\n2. How does Bayesian optimization (BO) compare to other calibration methods?\n3. What is trust-region BO (TuRBO)?\n4. How do they handle high-dimensional parameter spaces?\n5. What accuracy improvements do they achieve?\n6. What are the key lessons for calibrating DES simulators?"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6906,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ET3SZbYVS2gFM9krv6mM9v","session_id":"6b183c99-f74b-427d-be1f-597eb641e46a","uuid":"d295b7ce-f5a4-4e15-8c48-24f38acf5e2d"}
