{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01STRy9gKePGtgqCPHhXaVrn","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n**Round 3 strategic context:** The literature survey reveals a critical insight — the 31,906% TTFT error is almost certainly a *simulation fidelity* problem (request lifecycle mismatch), not a step-time problem. FairBatching (2025) shows that a 3-coefficient linear model (`a + b*new_tokens + c*total_context`) achieves ±1.3% per-step error. Meanwhile, Revati (2025) demonstrates that reimplemented schedulers inevitably diverge from real vLLM. The winning Round 3 strategy must attack TTFT at the simulation level while also fixing the step-time model's missing total-context feature.\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n\nNow let me check if the round3 directory already exists and what's in it."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b183c99-f74b-427d-be1f-597eb641e46a","uuid":"291f4423-264a-4004-8507-84faad1090f2"}
