{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_bdrk_01H9PsX8LAU9rqdCiLPzrRrS","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"WP1 and WP2 for Round 3 are complete. Here's a summary of what was produced:\n\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\n**Round 3 strategy is fundamentally different from Rounds 1-2.** Prior rounds focused exclusively on step-time ML models (Ridge, XGBoost, regime ensembles). Round 3 recognizes that the dominant error (31,906% TTFT) is a simulation-fidelity problem, not a step-time problem. The three ideas form a complementary pipeline: Idea 1 isolates the error source (workload spec vs scheduling), Idea 2 fixes the step-time formulation using literature-validated techniques, and Idea 3 optimizes the full coefficient set against the metric that actually matters (E2E error).\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\n\n## WP1+WP2 Completion Summary\n\n### Artifacts Created\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `round3/research.md` | 3 research ideas with literature citations (12 papers surveyed) |\n| `round3/idea-1-trace-replay/HYPOTHESIS.md` | 3 sub-hypotheses: trace replay reduces TTFT, error attribution, workload-spec diagnosis |\n| `round3/idea-2-total-context-model/HYPOTHESIS.md` | 3 sub-hypotheses: FairBatching formulation, feature scaling comparison, BLIS E2E + 34B investigation |\n| `round3/idea-3-e2e-calibration/HYPOTHESIS.md` | 3 sub-hypotheses: trace-replay E2E optimization, workload-spec E2E optimization, additive corrections |\n| `round3/.phase1_done` | Marker for orchestrator |\n\n### Three Ideas\n\n1. **Trace-Driven Simulation with Lifecycle Replay** — Attacks BC-1 (TTFT mismatch) by replaying exact ground-truth arrivals in BLIS, eliminating workload-spec generation as an error source. Low risk, uses existing infrastructure.\n\n2. **Total-Context Linear Model with Feature Scaling** — Attacks BC-2 (KV feature scaling) by using FairBatching's validated 3-coefficient formulation (`a + b*new_tokens + c*total_context`) and proper feature scaling (StandardScaler/log-transform). Also investigates the 34B anomaly (BC-3).\n\n3. **End-to-End Calibration via Direct E2E Objective** — Attacks all BCs by optimizing coefficients directly against BLIS E2E error using CMA-ES, bypassing per-step MAPE as an intermediate metric. Consumes outputs from Ideas 1 and 2.\n\n**Not proceeding to WP3** as instructed. The `.phase1_done` marker signals the orchestrator that WP1+WP2 are complete and WP3 phases can begin."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b183c99-f74b-427d-be1f-597eb641e46a","uuid":"a0debf78-5e1c-4e16-b689-f194cbd35942"}
